parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "DRAM",
"other_software": [
"Miniconda2"
],
"resource_requirements": [
"nodes=1",
"ntasks=5",
"time=7-50:00:00",
"mem=10gb",
"mail-type=BEGIN,END,FAIL",
"mail-user=jrodram@colostate.edu",
"partition=wrighton-hi"
]
}
```

This script runs the **DRAM** application. 

The script utilizes the **Miniconda2** environment to activate the DRAM environment. It requests one node, five cores per node, and 10GB of memory, with a time limit of 7 days and 50 hours. 

The script also configures email notifications for the job's beginning, end, and failure. It runs on the **wrighton-hi** partition. 

The script's purpose appears to be to run the "distill" function of the DRAM application, using a custom distillate module and an input file.
